      "type": "text",
      "x": 0, "y": 0, "width": 24, "height": 6,
      "properties": {
        "markdown": "# NAVADA Edge Network — Command Centre\n**Director**: Lee Akpareva | **Chief of Staff**: Claude AI | **Domain**: navada-edge-server.uk\n\n---\n\n## Network Architecture\nNAVADA Edge is a distributed AI infrastructure mesh spanning 5 nodes connected via Tailscale VPN. The network operates a primary always-on server (HP), a cloud compute node (AWS EC2), a database and log analytics node (Oracle Cloud), a development workstation with local AI inference (ASUS), and a mobile command interface (iPhone via Telegram).\n\n**Compute Mesh** | HP NAVADA (Primary, always-on, ethernet) | EC2 t3.medium (AWS eu-west-2, auto-sleep enabled) | Oracle VM (OCI, E5.Flex, ELK stack) | ASUS NAVADA2025 (Dev, Intel Ultra 7, local YOLO)\n\n**AI Services** | Bedrock Claude Sonnet 4.6 + Opus 4.6 (eu-west-2) | YOLOv8n Object Detection (ASUS local :8765 primary, SageMaker Serverless fallback) | Rekognition v7 (face collection navada-faces) | Vision Lambda Router (5 endpoints) | ChromaDB Cloud (RAG + semantic cache)\n\n**Connectivity** | Tailscale mesh (5 nodes) | Cloudflare Tunnel (api.navada-edge-server.uk) | Nginx reverse proxy (HP Docker) | SSM Session Manager (EC2, no SSH required)\n\n**CI/CD** | Jenkins (HP Docker :8082) | PM2 process management (HP 12 services, EC2 3 services) | Auto-deploy via git poll\n\n**Failover** | HP (Primary) to Oracle VM (auto 15min) to EC2 (manual) | Cloudflare DNS switching | State sync every 5 min\n\n**Cost Controls** | EC2 auto-sleep (CPU <5% for 30min) | Daily budget USD 1.50 with email alerts | SageMaker scales to zero | Lambda free tier"
      }
    },
